<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Nessie</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A tension in antitrust law is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It is illegal for two companies to ge=
t together and agree =E2=80=9Cwe won=E2=80=99t cut our price below $10 if y=
ou won=E2=80=99t.=E2=80=9D That is a classic conspiracy in restraint of tra=
de.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If the two companies just inde=
pendently decide to price their thing at $10, that=E2=80=99s fine, <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32923785.285424/aHR0cHM6L=
y9zd2Fuc29uaGF0Y2guY29tL25vZGUvMTA2/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbd23dc0e" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> that=E2=80=99s just competition</a>. But in practice, two companies se=
lling the same thing are probably going to sell it for around the same pric=
e. Also in most cases it=E2=80=99s not like the prices are=C2=A0<em>secret<=
/em>. So if you monitor your competitors=E2=80=99 prices, and set your pric=
e where they set theirs, that=E2=80=99s probably fine. (Not legal advice!)=
=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">These things are not=C2=A0<=
em>so=C2=A0</em>different? If your competitor calls you up and says =E2=80=
=9Cour price is $10, is yours also $10?=E2=80=9D and you say =E2=80=9Csure =
$10 is good=E2=80=9D then you are conspiring. If your competitor just puts =
out a sign saying =E2=80=9Cour price is $10=E2=80=9D and you drive by and s=
ee the sign and put up your own sign saying =E2=80=9Cour price is $10,=E2=
=80=9D then you are competing. But the content of those two things is kind =
of the same?</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So the US Federal Trade Commission has <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32923785.285424/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuZnRjLmdvdi9hZHZpY2UtZ3VpZGFuY2UvY29tcGV0aXRpb24tZ3VpZGFuY2UvZ3VpZGUt=
YW50aXRydXN0LWxhd3MvZGVhbGluZ3MtY29tcGV0aXRvcnMvcHJpY2UtZml4aW5n/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBd6b3474e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;"> this question and answer on its website</=
a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Q: Our company monitors competitors' ads, and =
we sometimes offer to match special discounts or sales incentives for consu=
mers. Is this a problem?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A: No. Matching competitors' pricing may be go=
od business, and occurs often in highly competitive markets. Each company i=
s free to set its own prices, and it may charge the same price as its compe=
titors as long as the decision was not based on any agreement or coordinati=
on with a competitor.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But if you are monitoring their prices and the=
y are monitoring your prices and you are always responding to each other, t=
hat might not be =E2=80=9Cagreement,=E2=80=9D but is it =E2=80=9Ccoordinati=
on=E2=80=9D? The better you get at monitoring and unilaterally predicting t=
heir prices, the more it might look, to the naked eye,=C2=A0like coordinati=
on. Guess who=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/32923785.285424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9yZXRhaWwvYW1he=
m9uLXVzZWQtc2VjcmV0LXByb2plY3QtbmVzc2llLWFsZ29yaXRobS10by1yYWlzZS1wcmljZXMt=
NmM1OTM3MDY_bW9kPWhwX2xlYWRfcG9zMg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1c6f7c91" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> really good at it</a>?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Amazon.com=C2=A0used an algorithm code-named =
=E2=80=9CProject Nessie=E2=80=9D to test how much it could raise prices in =
a way that competitors would follow, according to redacted portions of the =
Federal Trade Commission=E2=80=99s monopoly lawsuit against the company.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The algorithm helped Amazon improve its profit=
 on items across shopping categories, and because of the power the company =
has in e-commerce, led competitors to raise their prices and charge custome=
rs more, according to people familiar with the allegations in the complaint=
. In instances where competitors didn=E2=80=99t raise their prices to Amazo=
n=E2=80=99s level, the algorithm=E2=80=94which is no longer in use=E2=80=94=
automatically returned the item to its normal price point.</p>
</blockquote>
